=== Assignment 3 ===
If enemy flags exist, the robot tank finds a path to an enemy flag using A-star search.  If enemy flags don't exist, the robot tank finds a path to the local player's tank using A-star search.  Implements A-star search using the [http://code.google.com/p/yagsbpl/ YAGSBPL] template-based library.

=== Installing ===
# Download the BZFlag 2.4.0 source (not the installer/binary)
# Extract the source files into a directory (<code>$BZFLAG_HOME</code>)
# Place the provided files in the corresponding directories within <code>$BZFLAG_HOME</code>, replacing some existing files
# Build BZFlag as normal

=== Running ===
* <code>$BZFS_BIN</code> - the path to the BZFlag server executable
* <code>$BZFLAG_BIN</code> - the path to the BZFlag client executable
# <code>$BZFS_BIN/bzfs -cr</code>
# <code>$BZFLAG_BIN/bzflag -solo 1</code>

